About the separator question, I think we are wasting time on nothing;
even in pure C, writing a parser for any string with integers separed by any char, it is matter of 5 min for 5 rows:
while ((*s)!=0){
  v[k]=0;
  while (((*s)>='0')&&((*s)<='9')){ v[k]=10*v[k]+(*s)-'0';s++; }
  k++;
  if (*s!=0) s++;
}
so, let me leave it that way, since someone will always prefer "the other way out".

The parsing phase is really not part of the puzzle, the fun is on the topology problem itselh
